á» trÃªn ta Ä‘Ã£ xem xÃ©t \(Y|X\) vÃ  chá»‰ ra ráº±ng giÃ¡ trá»‹ \(\alpha\) mÃ  ta quan tÃ¢m hoÃ n toÃ n cÃ³ thá»ƒ tÃ­nh toÃ¡n dá»±a vÃ o sufficient statistic \(TC\) vÃ  nÃ³ cÃ³ thá»ƒ Ä‘Æ°á»£c tÃ­nh trong báº¥t ká»³ khÃ´ng gian nÃ o (interventional hoáº·c observational). \[ \Bbb{P}_{\varnothing}(T=1) = \pi, \\ X|(T,F_T = \varnothing) \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu_T,\Sigma) \] vá»›i \(\pi \in (0,1)\), \(\{\mu_{t} \in \mathbb{R}^{p\times 1}:t=0,1\}\) vÃ  \(\Sigma \in \mathbb{R}^{p\times p}\). NhÆ° váº­y trong khÃ´ng gian observational ta cÃ³

Viá»‡c cÃ²n láº¡i lÃ  ta pháº£i chá»‰ ra ráº±ng \(\beta^{\top}X\) lÃ  má»™t minimal sufficient statistic cá»§a \(\alpha\).

Chá»©ng minh: \(\beta^{\top}X\) lÃ  má»™t minimal sufficient statistic

Láº¥y \(\tau =T\), ta cÃ³
